Third-party components

This MIT license covers only the original source code of highcharts-studio
(the Streamlit application and its helpers). It does NOT relicense, and does
NOT grant you any rights to, the third-party components this project depends on
at runtime. Two of them are proprietary and separately licensed:

  * Highcharts JS (loaded from the Highcharts CDN) and the Highcharts export
    server are proprietary software owned by Highsoft AS. They are free for
    personal and non-commercial use; commercial use requires a paid Highcharts
    license obtained from Highsoft.

  * highcharts-core (the "Highcharts for Python" toolkit) is proprietary
    software governed by the Highcharts for Python Toolkit License, owned by
    HCP LLC and distributed by Highsoft. Its use is subject to that license
    (which itself presupposes a Highcharts Software license — a paid one for
    commercial use, or a Personal/Educational license otherwise).

If you use, fork, or deploy this project, you are responsible for obtaining
whatever Highcharts and Highcharts-for-Python licenses your usage requires.
Streamlit (Apache-2.0) and pandas (BSD-3-Clause) are permissively licensed and
carry no such restriction.
